70 «L’alto disio che mo t’infiamma e urge, 71 d’aver notizia di ciò che tu vei, 72 tanto mi piace più quanto più turge;
73 ma di quest’ acqua convien che tu bei 74 prima che tanta sete in te si sazi»: 75 così mi disse il sol de li occhi miei.

query.result:
**English:**
70 "The lofty desire that now inflames and urges you 71 to have knowledge of that which you will see, 72 pleases me all the more the more it swells;
73 but it is necessary that you drink of this water 74 before such thirst in you is sated": 75 thus spoke to me the sun of my eyes.
**Sanskrit:**
70 "Uccaiḥ icchā yā adhunā tvām prajvalayati ca pracodati ca, 71 jñātum tat kiṃ yat tvam drakṣyasi, 72 tām adhikaṃ priyāṃ manye yathādhikaṃ vardhate;
73 apitu anena ambunā avasyam te pātavyam 74 pūrvam yāvat tāvadīyaḥ tṛṣṇā tvayi na pūrṇā bhavati": 75 evam mama netrāṇāṃ sūryaḥ mayā uktaḥ.
